Package: LibeRator
Type: Package
Title: Adaptive Therapeutic Optimisation and Recommendation
Version: 0.2.5
Authors@R: person("Sven C.", "van Dijkman",
    email = "svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sven C. van Dijkman [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sven C. van Dijkman <svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Research and teaching tools for longitudinal model-informed
    precision dosing. Maintains encrypted, auditable patient timelines;
    resolves time-varying and intermittently observed covariates without
    silently inventing values; performs automatic-differentiation-backed
    Bayesian individualisation; represents changing patient parameters; and
    compares clinically feasible regimens against versioned pharmacokinetic,
    pharmacodynamic, biomarker, and composite endpoints. Integrates with
    LibeRation models, the LibeRary model catalogue, and local or remote
    LibeRties queues. It is not a medical device and must not be used as a
    substitute for qualified clinical judgement.
